The paper discusses a decentralized platform for transactive microgrids that involves cyber and physical systems, financial markets, and privacy-preserving mechanisms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), which deals with privacy and security issues in computer systems. The paper also involves distributed systems and control, which suggests the category cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses safety requirements and power flow constraints, which are related to control systems, suggesting the category cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves optimization and matching algorithms, which suggests the category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves cyber-physical systems, which suggests the category cs.CY (Computers and Society).
